<br>
I know that there are ALOT of &quot;Rules&quot;, &quot;DO's&quot; and especially &quot;NOT DO's&quot; associated with Dragon hunts and plane raids, and i was hoping that our experienced hunters/raiders would share some of the knowledge they have accumulated. So that I and my fellow mages wont be a complete Newbie on their first plane raid <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .<br>
<br>
This could very well become a great library submission thread <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Thank you in advance ! <p>- Helf PetCommander<BR> Excellent Magician of Bristlebane <BR>
Proud member of Orbis Honesti</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Dimuyen</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(7/20/00 8:43:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Here's a few</span><hr size=1> NO PETS until raid leaders say it's ok.  <br>
<br>
When you do summon a pet make sure you set it to /notaunt or you will get summoned and maybe killed.<br>
<br>
Keep track of your pet.  If you're 46+ you should know how to do this...but I've seen some poor examples of pet control even at that level before (but rare).  dont let your pet chase things...not even if you're sure it'll be ok.<br>
<br>
if you're using cancel magic spells....USE THEM EARLY.  Make sure you're not annulling other people's debuffs.<br>
<br>
this really applies to all classes:  Use your Assist &lt;main assist&gt; button!  do not attack unless you have just hit your button and acquired a target.<br>
<br>
no fire spells on naggy.<br>
<br>
I may think of more later.<br>
<br>
oh yeah...on mass death situations give everyone a mod rod.<br>
<br>
(btw...this one is good for other situations.)  As soon as you die and appear at bind point...summon something.  That way if you get killed you'll have an item and will leave a corpse behind.  Do this for others as well.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
