<br>
Hate is where your armor drops (Apothic Armor).  Hate is pie compared to Fear because Hate has safe spots as where Fear does not.  Hate does have really annoying mobs, i.e.: Spite Golems (100% Magic Resistant, they are also shamans so they have sow on) and the other mob is Cleric of Innoruuk (Yes, he CHs himself, you got to stun/nuke him to hell at 1/4 life to prevent him to do so).  In addition, if a mob you're killing is near a Cleric of Innoruuk, that cleric will CH it, trust me, it has happened to me where we were killing a Spite Golem and people didn't listen and it was CHed 3 times before we had a train.<br>
<br>
On my server, Xegony, there aren't too mages coming up on Hate raids so usually at least 2 of them will get a piece if the zone is cleared.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps for Hate.<br>
<br>
Later <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :smokin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smokin.gif ALT=":smokin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p><c><font size="+1"><b><font color="darkred"><font face="papyrus">Abyen D'ahr<br>53 Elementalist<br>Xegony</p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uabyendahr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abyen Dahr</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 7/29/00 4:38:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvylaek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vylaek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>   <font color=#333333>(7/30/00 6:36:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Request for &quot;Alternate plane mage behaviour guide&q</span><hr size=1> I was in Hate the other night, the only mage there, and two apothic robes dropped. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   It's nice to finally have one, along with a backup robe which can be hard to get.<br>
<br>
We started with 24 people, and when we finished clearing, we had 12, so my role was as diversified as it can be.<br>
<br>
For most of the night, I was able to use my pet, so I had to be mindful of him.  We had only one shaman, so I was on malise duty -- which is easier in fear than it is in hate.  <br>
<br>
Malise duty consists of casting the highest level spell you have in the malise line you have.  Once a monster is malised, you have you announce it to the raid with an ooc social that spits out something like, &quot;===MALISEMENT===&quot;.  This is an easy job, but you have to learn which monsters you can malise easily, and which monsters to give up easily on. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   You can also start malising mez'd monsters before combat is initiated on them.<br>
<br>
Along with all of this, I was also nuking for a good part of the night.  Later on, with our numbers low, I was put on modrod duty, making sure there were plenty of mod rods on the ground for clerics and encs to use.  Our main cleric has that blue kunark ruby bp clone that regens, so it worked out nicely.  I had a bard in my group with manasong 2, and an enc casting clarity 2 on me, so it worked out nicely.<br>
<br>
This doesn't sound like a lot of work, but you have to switch between two or three sets of hotkeys pretty quickly, and with the modrod duty, I was kept really busy.<br>
<br>
That was the most fun I've had in Hate.  I really enjoyed being part of a small group, and I enjoy being on malise duty..  It beats just medding and nuking throughout the night.<br>
<br>
 <p>Vylaek<BR>
Dark Elf Magician<BR>
