<br>
Like they said above, expect to die, sometimes a lot.  It depends upon how good your raid leader is and how well the party works as a team, how many enchanters you have, and some luck.  As mages we have mostly taken over the Malosi role in raids but coordinate with any shamans, never hurts to have 2 people doing it.  Fire can be used on all the mobs here.  I also do not turn off taunt, any damage my pet can take is less for the tanks, I get summoned a lot but rarely get hurt.<br>
<br>
Hate.<br>
<br>
After the party gets set in their camp you can pet up.  Keep a close eye on your pet and be ready to have it bach off if it starts to run.  When fighting Spites, if your the only mage there, assist the spite, and do damage shields on the tanks.  You really need more than 1 person doing Malosi here as you will get resisted a lot.  After Malosi fire is good here also, if you are fighting near a wall you can go up the wall a little ways and use Lava Bolt.<br>
<br>
Dragons,<br>
<br>
