<br>
In Hate, generally people don't die getting to the west wall camp -- near the sw corner.  Fastest I've heard it cleared with Inno up is 4 hours, I was on a raid that cleared in in around 5 with inno up.  In the last two raids I've been on there, there's been one mass death, life is pretty easy.<br>
<br>
Most people do fear by getting a cleric or a monk with a rez stick camped -- or a necro now, heh -- camped in the north wall camp.  Everyone else basically makes a mad dash for the camp, getting as close to possible without camping.  Quite a few people die, but are rez'd as the raid goes on.  If you're not a vital class and you're killed by the gate, don't expect to be res'd fast.  Fear takes much longer to clear and is a much tougher break.  Cazic is tougher than Inno, and it's not unusual for him to agro the zone, meaning everyone has to camp.<br>
<br>
I really don't see how anyone can consider fear to be as easy as hate.  To me, there's no comparison. <p>Vylaek, <BR>
Level 50 Dark Elf Magician<BR>
Pikka Chu, <BR>
Level 20 Ogre Warrior<BR>
